```
int[] arr = new int[10];
```

If I want to then populate this array, I can easily do so:
```
arr[1] = 5;
arr[2] = 10;
// etc.
```

My question is, what if I want to create an array of, let&#39;s say, objects of class Card. Each I want to initialize with values in a programmatic way. For example, let&#39;s say I want to create a Deck of cards, as such:

```
Card[][] deck;

for(int i = DIAMONDS; i &lt;= SPADES; ++i) {
   for(int i = ACE; i &lt;= KING; ++i) {
        deck[i][j] = new Card(i, j);
